records.full_caption: Figure 1. (a) Synthetic scheme showing the progression from the monomer, β-myrcene, to poly(myrcene-epoxide) (PME) via epoxidation, and the ring opening addition of hydroxy-TEMPO (H-TEMPO) using the organobase catalyst DBU to create the PME-H-TEMPO species (PME-TEMPO) via free radical polymerization (FR). (b) Representative 1H NMR spectra of PBM, PME, and PME-TEMPO. (c) Representative SEC chromatograms showing that the number-average diameter of the material increases at each synthetic step.
records.caption: Representative 1H NMR spectra of PBM, PME, and PME-TEMPO.

records.full_caption: Figure 2. Representative cyclic voltammograms (CVs) of FR, FRL, and RAFT PME-TEMPO species showing the oxidation and reduction reactions of the TEMPO radical.
